cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.DS

The paper discusses a machine learning algorithm (Kohonen's self-organizing map) and proposes a new algorithm that improves its efficiency. This suggests that the paper belongs to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The algorithm is applied to clustering problems, which could fall under natural language processing (cs.CL) or computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses implementation methods that reduce running time, which could also fall under the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
